  "prompt": "Why is rhinovirus harmful? How can it be treated?",
  "response": "Rhinovirus, commonly known as the common cold virus, can be harmful for several reasons:\n\nHarmful aspects:\n1. Causes respiratory tract infections\n2. Triggers inflammation in nasal passages\n3. Can worsen existing respiratory conditions like asthma\n4. Leads to symptoms such as:\n- Runny nose\n- Congestion\n- Sore throat\n- Cough\n- Mild fever\n\nTreatment approaches:\n1. Symptomatic relief\n- Over-the-counter decongestants\n- Pain relievers\n- Antihistamines\n- Nasal sprays\n\n2. Rest and hydration\n- Adequate sleep\n- Drinking plenty of fluids\n- Supporting immune system recovery\n\n3. Prevention strategies\n- Frequent hand washing\n- Avoiding close contact with infected individuals\n- Maintaining good hygiene\n- Boosting immune system through nutrition\n\n4. No specific antiviral treatment\n- Virus typically resolves on its own\n- Antibiotics are ineffective against viral infections\n\n5. Potential complications management\n- Monitor for secondary bacterial infections\n- Seek medical attention if symptoms worsen or persist\n\nWhile generally mild, rhinovirus can cause significant discomfort and potential complications for vulnerable populations.",
